  "original_title": "\u0db7\u0dd6\u0db8\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd9\u0dbd\u0dca \u0db8\u0dd2\u0dbd\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dd9\u0da7 \u0d85\u0db1\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dca\u0daf\u0dcf\u0db8 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0da9\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dbb\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The price of kerosene will be increased tomorrow",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Energy Minister Kanchana Wijesekera said in Parliament today (5) that the price of kerosene will definitely be increased the day after tomorrow.",
        "He said this in the debate on orders under the Foreign Exchange Act.",
        "The minister mentioned that kerosene is now sold at 87 rupees and the corporation spends 420 rupees on kerosene.",
        "He said that if the fuel is distributed properly, there should be no loss.",
        "\"The corporation has been giving at a low price until now. Now it can't be done.",
        "\"When the price of crude oil is increased, they will accuse the government of hitting the fishermen. On the other hand, they will shout to give fuel.",
        "If you want to give the fuel, you have to sell it without loss. We don't get grace periods to pay off loans now.",
        "Collecting rupees like dollars is also a problem today. That is why it is suggested that the credit limit of the Petroleum Corporation should be increased. The Prime Minister is working for it."
      ],
